definition.value: Any capillary endothelial cell that is part of a lung.

value.value: A fibroblast that is located in the renal cortical interstitium.

Renal cortical fibroblasts have key roles in mediating intercellular communication with neighboring/infiltrating cells and extracellular matrix and maintenance of renal tissue architecture. They additionally have an endocrine function in the production of epoetin.
A lymphocyte located in blood.

Any cell that is located within the interstitium between the cells most prominent in defining a given tissue. "Interstitial cell" is a morphological term and refers to a variety of cells with differing origins and phenotypes.
A ciliated cell of the respiratory system. Ciliated cells are present in airway epithelium.
A dental pulp cell that possesses stem-cell-like qualities, including self-renewal capability and multi-lineage differentiation.
A ciliated cell of the endometrial epithelium. The cilia of this cell type help move mucus from glandular tissue of the endometrium.
In human samples, the expression of FOXJ1 protein, a regulator for motile cilia with epithelial lineage identity, has been noted.

label.value: serous secreting cell of bronchus submucosal gland

value.value: A(n) serous secreting cell that is part of a(n) bronchus submucosal gland.

label.value: vein endothelial cell of respiratory system

value.value: A(n) vein endothelial cell that is part of a(n) respiratory system.
A smooth muscle cell that is part of a bronchiole.
A megakaryocyte that is resident in the lung connective tissue.

label.value: mucus secreting cell of trachea gland

value.value: A mucus secreting cell that is part of a submucosal gland of the trachea.

label.value: mucus secreting cell of bronchus submucosal gland

value.value: A mucus secreting cell of a submucosal gland of the bronchus.

label.value: mucus secreting cell of tracheobronchial tree submucosal gland

value.value: A mucus secreting cell of a submucosal gland of the tracheobronchial tree.
A taste receptor cell that is part of a taste bud of a tongue.
A neuron that releases catecholamine as a neurotransmitter.

Frequently used when describing the developing nervous system in zebrafish. A catecholaminergic neuron expresses tyrosine hydroxylase (TH), tyrosine hydroxylase 2 (TH2), aromatic amino acid decarboxylase (AADC), dopamine b-hydroxylase (DBH), and phenylethanolamine-N-methyl transferase (PEMT), which are enzymes necessary for catecholamine synthesis.
The length of a body that includes the tail.

definition.value: This is measured from the snout to the end of the tail along the anterior-posterior axis in four-legged vertebrates.

value.value: The length of a body that excludes a tail.

definition.value: This is measured from the snout to before the tail, usually ending at the anus in four-legged vertebrates.

The length of a hindfoot that excludes the nail.
